Correlations of visceral fat accumulation and atherosclerosis in Japanese patients with type 2 diabetes mellitus. We tested the hypothesis that increased abdominal visceral fat accumulation (VFA) is associated with insulin resistance and aortic stiffness in patients with type 2 diabetes mellitus not receiving insulin treatment. The study consisted of 22 Japanese patients with type 2 diabetes mellitus and high VFA (> or =100 cm(2) age, 61 +/- 7 years